    "If we sampled 120 people, and assumed a split in the preferences between Biden and Trump of 50: 50, we would be able to produce an estimate of the preferences that is, at most, 5 points off the true value with probability 0.86.",
    "The key take-away from sampling theory is that it is possible to accurately and precisely measure public opinion by simply looking at small random samples from the population.",
    "However, traditional polling practices fail.",
    "This is particularly evident in the context of pre-election opinion polling.",
    "While there are competing hypotheses for why pre-election polling fails, recent evidence has shown that the non-representativeness of samples is the major culprit, 4."
  ],
